public final class SerializableUnmodifiableHashMap<K extends Serializable,V extends Serializable>
extends HashMap<K,V>
implements SerializableMap<K,V>, Cloneable

Same as an unmodifiable HashMap, except that this class promises to be fully serializable.

The wrapped sets are stored locally in order to improve performance. This is transient in order to avoid double serialization. After deserialization, that local state is lazily reinitialized.

Author:
Thomas Jensen
